# **TYRANID HIVE SPECIAL RULES**

### **Synapse Control**

All Tyranids are united by the potent psychic imperatives of their shared hive mind.  Some of the larger, more intelligent Tyranid Creatures have vastly expanded synapse networks within their cortex that act as a psychic conduit for the directives of the Hive Mind, overruling the natural instincts of nearby Tyranid Creatures.  
Any Tyranid units within 12” of a creature with the **Synapse Node** Hive Mind Power (including the psyker itself) are within Synapse Control range and never have to fall back and are assumed to automatically pass any Morale checks they are required to take, even against attacks which normally force their target to fall back with no test taken. Any Pinning tests and tests to regroup it has to make are also passed automatically.

### **Fast and Deadly**

Tyranid swarms move quickly across even the most inhospitable and broken ground under the mental lash of the hive mind.  In battle, Tyranids attack on the run and often creatures are trampled, forced over cliffs, or drowned by the animalistic stampede as the swarm races forward.  
To represent this, Tyranids with the ***Fast and Deadly*** special rule always roll one D6 more than normal when checking to see how far they can move through Difficult Terrain.  However, if a Tyranid brood of eight or more models rolls two or more 6s on the dice, it suffers one wound in the stampede (saving throws apply as normal).  
Synapse creatures still get to roll the extra dice but will not suffer wounds when moving through difficult terrain due to their direct control of the creatures around them.

### **Brood Juggernaut**

Tyranids with the Brood Juggernaut Special Rule are subject to the following:

* Brood Juggernauts can join units of other Tyranid Creatures, but they may always be picked out as a separate target for enemy shooting unless the unit contains Tyrant Guards.  A Tyranid unit including a model with the ***Brood Juggernaut*** special rule is limited to moving and assaulting at the speed of the slowest model in the unit.  
* Brood Juggernauts have the ***Fearless*** special rule.  
* Brood Juggernauts can always choose to shoot at a different target to the unit they have joined.  
* Brood Juggernauts may re-roll the dice for moving through difficult terrain unless they have joined a unit.  
* Brood Juggernauts count as a unit of troops for victory conditions, so they can capture objectives and count as surviving troops in a Meat Grinder battle.

