### **Chameleonic Skin**

A unit entirely composed of models with the ***Chameleonic Skin*** special rule does not scatter when arriving via Deep Strike

### **Spore Mines**

Spore Mines are very basic, geno-modified organisms which the Tyranids use as “living bombs” most commonly launched from living artillery pieces called Biovores.  The mines are engorged sacs full of chemicals, viruses, toxins, and poisons that drift slowly in the air currents, with nests of sensitive feelers dangling below questing for the heat and vibration of possible targets.  Although it’s possible to avoid the attention of a Spore Mine by moving carefully and quietly, weapons discharges and other violent noises will stimulate a detonation with often fatal results.

* **Movement**: Spore Mines drift 1D6” in a random direction in each Tyranid Movement Phase, as determined by rolling the Scatter Dice.  On a roll of a Hit, the Tyranid player may choose the direction of movement of the Spore Mine.  Unlike most models, a Spore Mine can move within 1” of enemy models and vehicles during it’s movement and if it makes contact with an enemy model it detonates.  Spore Mines, however, cannot make Charges.  
* **Detonation**: If a Spore Mine makes contact with an enemy, or an enemy unit or vehicle shoots while within 2” of it, the mine explodes.  Resolves the detonation after the unit/vehicle’s firing is complete. Place the template or blast marker over the spot where the mine explodes and resolve the results according to its type as described in the profile.  If a mine is reduced to 0 wounds or otherwise killed, it will explode as detailed above.  An enemy unit may divide it’s fire between all Spore Mine Models within 6” of its members and treat them as a single target for shooting purposes.  Spore Mines can also be detonated by Synaptic Control.  
* **Morale**:  Being essentially mindless, a Spore Mine never has to fall back and is assumed to automatically pass any Morale Checks it is required to take, even against attacks which normally cause their target to fall back with no test taken.  Spore Mines cannot be Pinned.  For the purpose of mission objectives, Spore Mines cannot capture objectives and do not count as surviving troops.

### **Tyranid Psyker (MLX)**

Given their unique relationship with the Warp through the Hive Mind, Tyranid psykers are generally immune to conventional *Perils of the Warp*. They do not risk possession by daemons, insanity, or the Warp rifts that might affect other psykers.  Because of this, a Tyranid Psyker will never roll for Perils of the Warp on the Core Rulebook table.  Instead, they must always roll a d6 on the Synaptic Overload table shown below.  
Models with the ***Tyranid Psyker*** special rule are treated as if they had the ***Psyker*** special rule for all rules interactions, but are not limited to 1 power per ML.  They instead must buy their Hive Mind Powers as wargear for points.  Models with the ***Tyranid Psyker*** special rule may only know Hive Mind Powers and may not take powers from other lists.

