### **Pheromone Trail**

If a friendly unit with the Tyranids Faction arrives on the battlefield via Deep Strike, it will not scatter so long as the first model in the unit is placed within 6" of a model with this special rule. Note that the model with the ***Pheromone Trail*** special rule must already be on the table at the start of the turn for this ability to be used.

### **Psyker Brood**

Among the countless bio-forms created by the Tyranid Hive Mind, some are bred specifically to harness the destructive potential of psychic energy. These creatures, known collectively as the Psyker Brood, are not individual psychic entities but rather clusters of lesser synaptic creatures, each linked in a single telepathic web. The Hive Mind uses these broods as extensions of its own immense psychic power, channeling its will through them to overwhelm enemies, unleash psychic storms, or warp reality itself.  
A Psyker Brood is a special type of psyker where multiple models in the unit are collectively treated as a single psyker for purposes of mastery level and available powers.  The unit takes psychic tests using the highest leadership within the unit (an attached Brood Juggernaut’s leadership is never used for the psychic test).  If the unit suffers from perils of the warp, the unit’s owner chooses a model in the unit to suffer the effects.  Models with the ***Psyker Brood*** special rule have the ***Shadow in the Warp*** special rule.  A unit with the ***Psyker Brood*** special rule is treated as having the ***Brotherhood of Psykers*** special rule for all rules interactions.

### **Shadow in the Warp**

The constant hum of the Hive Mind drowns out psychic connections, reducing even the most powerful psykers to disoriented, ineffective shadows of their former selves. As the Tyranid presence grows stronger, their prey find it increasingly difficult to access the Warp, and mental assaults glance harmlessly off their mindless predators.  
All enemy Psykers within 6" times the Mastery Level (ML1=6”, ML2=12”, etc.) of any Tyranid model with the ***Shadow in the Warp*** special rule suffer a \-2 penalty to their Leadership when taking Psychic tests. In addition, any Maledictions automatically fail to affect Tyranid models within 6” times the Mastery Level of any Tyranid model with the ***Shadow in the Warp*** special rule unless the caster rolls a 4+ on a D6.

